  'Understanding SMM7: A Student Guide',
  E'## SMM7 Student Guide\n\nThe Standard Method of Measurement (SMM7) is the **foundation** of quantity surveying measurement. This guide simplifies SMM7 for students.\n\n---\n\n### What is SMM7?\n\n**Definition:**\nA set of rules for measuring building works, ensuring consistency and accuracy in bills of quantities.\n\n**Why SMM7?**\n- Standardized measurement\n- Reduces disputes\n- Facilitates fair tendering\n- Enables cost comparison\n\n### Basic Principles\n\n**1. Measurement Rules:**\n- Always in metres (m)\n- Two decimal places\n- No deductions for small openings\n- Waste included in rates\n\n**2. Description Rules:**\n- Material first, then workmanship\n- Include thickness and type\n- Specify quality and finish\n- Reference specifications\n\n**3. Ordering:**\n- Logical sequence\n- Substructure first\n- Superstructure second\n- Finishes last\n\n### Common Measurements\n\n| Item | Unit | How to Measure |\n|------|------|----------------|\n| Excavation | m3 | L x W x D |\n| Concrete | m3 | L x W x D |\n| Blockwork | m2 | L x H |\n| Plastering | m2 | L x H |\n| Roofing | m2 | Plan area |\n\n### Taking-Off Process\n\n**Step 1: Dimensions Sheet**\n- Grid reference\n- Description\n- Dimensions (T, Q, D, M)\n- Squaring\n- Total\n\n**Step 2: Abstracting**\n- Group similar items\n- Calculate totals\n- Apply wastage\n\n**Step 3: Billing**\n- Transfer to BOQ\n- Write descriptions\n- Apply rates\n\n### Practice Example\n\n**Task: Measure a foundation**\n\n**Given:**\n- Length: 10m\n- Width: 0.9m\n- Depth: 1.2m\n\n**Taking-Off:**\nDescription: Excavate trench\nLength: 10.00m\nWidth: 0.90m\nDepth: 1.20m\nVolume: 10.00 x 0.90 x 1.20 = 10.80 m3\n\n### Key SMM7 Rules\n\n1. **Rule of Three**: If item is less than 3 dimensions, do not measure\n2. **Minimum Measurement**: 100mm (0.10m)\n3. **Waste**: Included in rates unless stated\n4. **Opening Deduction**: Only for openings over 0.3 m2\n5. **Corners**: Do not measure internal corners\n\n### Student Tips\n\n1. **Practice Daily**: Take-off one element per day\n2. **Use Real Drawings**: Practice with actual project drawings\n3. **Check Your Work**: Verify calculations\n4. **Learn the Rules**: Memorize key SMM7 rules\n5. **Ask Questions**: Consult lecturers and professionals\n\n> **Pro Tip**: SMM7 becomes intuitive with practice. Start with simple elements and build complexity gradually.\n\n### Common Student Mistakes\n\n1. **Wrong Units**: Using mm instead of m\n2. **Missing Items**: Forgetting to measure elements\n3. **Double Counting**: Measuring same item twice\n4. **Ignoring Deductions**: Not deducting openings\n5. **Poor Organization**: Messy dimension sheets',
  'article',
  ARRAY['smm7', 'student', 'measurement', 'beginner', 'exam-preparation'],
  TRUE
);
